AR in Journalism

Understanding the effect of Augmented Reality (AR) in Journalism.

Three reading modalities were defined:

  • Augmented Reality (AR)
  • Interactive visualizations (INTERACTIVE)
  • Static visualizations (STATIC)

Three pieces of information were defined:

  • Chemical bomb attack in Syria (Syria)
  • Youth soccer team reascue operation in Thailand (Thai)
  • Olympici skate figure Nathan Chen (Olympic)

Method

Align-and-rank data for non-paramentric ANOVA was applied to understand the effect of the reading modalities (see here for more information on the analysis method). The difference of difference method was employed to conduct post hoc pairwise comparison of levels within individual factors.

Sense of Presence

Studying the effect of the modality and piece of information in the subjects’ sense of presence.

i_cols = c('SUBJECT','CONDITION','PRESENCE_TOTAL_OLYM', 'PRESENCE_TOTAL_SYRIA', 
           'PRESENCE_TOTAL_THAI')
p_data = prepare_data(df_c, i_cols)
## [1] "Subjects removed because of missing values: 0"

Analysis of Variance

# Define model
m = art(value ~ modality * piece + (1|subject), data=p_data)
anova(m)
## Analysis of Variance of Aligned Rank Transformed Data
## 
## Table Type: Analysis of Deviance Table (Type III Wald F tests with Kenward-Roger df) 
## Model: Mixed Effects (lmer)
## Response: art(value)
## 
##                        F Df Df.res     Pr(>F)

## ---
## Signif. codes:   0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

The sense of presence is significalty affected by the reading modality, the piece of information, and the interaction between them.

There are a significant difference on the sense presence between AR and Interactive and AR and Static on the pieces Syria and Olympic. The difference in the narrative engagement and transportation is significant between AR and Interactive on the Olympic story. People reported a significant difference on the perceived learning between AR and Interactive on the Thai story. There are a significant difference on the knowledge gain between AR and Interactive on the story about Syria. Journalism norms are significantly different between AR and Interactive on the Thai story. Depending on the story, Thai or Syria, there are a significant difference in usability between AR and Interactive and AR and Static.
